headline: Harley-Davidson Achieves Milestone in Strategic Partnership with KKR and PIMCO with Completion of Sale of Residual Interests in Securitized Consumer Loan Receivables
summary: Harley-Davidson, Inc. (the "Company" or "Harley-Davidson") (NYSE: HOG) today announced the completion of the sale of its residual interests in securitized consumer loan receivables, marking a milestone in its strategic partnership with KKR, a leading global investment firm, and PIMCO, a global leader in active fixed income with expertise across public and private markets. headline: Half of Retirement Plan Participants Would Invest in Private Assets, Survey Finds
summary: The study should be welcome news to asset managers with funds that invest in private assets. They are on a path to win access to the nation’s 401(k)s.
